                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="11533" author="ojolly" created="Thu, 18 Nov 2004 04:20:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the xhtml/html code generated with selected=&quot;true&quot; is perfectly legal.&lt;br/&gt;
selected=&quot;selected&quot; is just a suggestion, any value assigned to the selected attribute makes it valid.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="11534" author="robmoore" created="Thu, 18 Nov 2004 04:42:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Browsers may handle any value for the attribute as sufficient, but the DTD actually specifies &apos;selected&apos; as the only valid value:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;!ELEMENT OPTION - O (#PCDATA)         &amp;#8211; selectable choice --&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;!ATTLIST OPTION&lt;br/&gt;
  %attrs;                              &amp;#8211; %coreattrs, %i18n, %events &amp;#8211;&lt;br/&gt;
  selected    (selected)     #IMPLIED&lt;br/&gt;
  disabled    (disabled)     #IMPLIED  &amp;#8211; unavailable in this context &amp;#8211;&lt;br/&gt;
  label       %Text;         #IMPLIED  &amp;#8211; for use in hierarchical menus &amp;#8211;&lt;br/&gt;
  value       CDATA          #IMPLIED  &amp;#8211; defaults to element content &amp;#8211;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;as taken from &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/strict.dtd&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/strict.dtd&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="11542" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Thu, 18 Nov 2004 18:45:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve changed the value to &quot;selected&quot; (in spring.vm and spring.ftl). If it works just as well as &quot;true&quot; and is arguably the correct value, there&apos;s no point in keeping the old value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="11551" author="robmoore" created="Fri, 19 Nov 2004 01:19:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Juergen!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
